title: $dom()
name: DOMList
description: Find elements using CSS Selector or create new element using HTML formatted string. DOMList using native .querySelectorAll(), so browser support really limited. Only for modern browsers (Chrome 31+, Firefox 33+, IE9+, Safari 7+).

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, CSS Selector string or HTML formatted string for create element.
CSS Selector String, HTML Element or DOMList to search in.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
// Find elements with tag-name 'button'.
var btn = $dom('button');

examples.title: Sample #2
examples.content: // Create new element using HTML formatted string. var btn = $dom('Anchor');

examples.title: Sample #3
Sample #4
examples.content:
// Find elements with tag-name 'button' from 'section' using CSS Selector string as context.
var bt = $dom('button', '.wrapper');

title: .addClass()
name: AddClass
description: Add class to class selected elements lists.

Parameter.description: String class name to add. If you want, you can use array to add multiple class.

title: .remClass()
name: RemClass
description: Remove class from selected elements class lists.

Parameter.description: String class name. You can use array if you want to use remove multiple class.

title: .toggleClass()
name: ToggleClass
description: Toggle class in selected elements class lists.

Parameter.description: String class name. You can use array if you want to toggle multiple class.

title: .attr()
name: Attr
description: Attribute getter and setter. You can set value with anythings. They will be automatically converted. When you get the value, they also will be converted automatically.

Parameter.description: String attribute name or Object containing list of attributes or Array containing attribute name list.
Attribute value.

examples.title: Sample #1
Sample #2
Sample #3
Sample #4
Sample #5

title: .children()
name: Children
description: Get child elements of first selected element.

title: .data()
name: Data
description: Get first selected element data or set all selected elements data.

Parameter.description: String data-attribute name. E.g. 'profile' for 'data-profile'.
Value to set. Leave blank if yout want to get the data-attribute-value.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('span').data('foo'); // Get value of 'data-foo'.
$dom('span').data('foo', {a: 1, b: 2}); // Set 'data-foo' value.

title: .find()
name: Find
description: Find elements from current selected elements.

Parameter.description: CSS Selector string.

title: .first()
name: First
description: Get the first child of selected elements. Return new DOMList object.

title: .firstChild()
name: FirstChild
description: Get the first child of the first selected elements. Return new DOMList object.

title: .each()
name: Iterator
description: Iterate each element inside DOMList.

Parameter.description: Function that handle each element. Element index will be provide as argument when calling handler.
Does iteration is reversed or not.

title: .last()
name: Last
description: Get the last child of selected elements. Return new DOMList object.

title: .lastChild()
name: LastChild
description: Get the last child of the first selected elements. Return new DOMList object.

title: .nth()
name: NTH
description: Get the selected elements by specific index. Return new DOMList object.

Parameter.description: Index number. Start from 0.

title: .nthChild()
name: NthChild
description: Get the child elements by specific index from the first selected elements. Return new DOMList object.

Parameter.description: Index number. Start from 0.

title: .prop()
name: Prop
description:
Get the first selected elements property value or set all selected elements property value.
If element also have attribute with that name, setting property will also set the attribute.

Parameter.description: String property name.
String property value.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('input[type="text"]').prop('value'); // Get value.
$dom('input[type="text"]').prop('value', 'Foo'); // Set value to Foo.

title: .remAttr()
name: RemAttr
description: Remove one or many attribute from selected elements.

Parameter.description:
String attribute name or array name list.
Use space to separate the attribute name for multiple removal. E.g 'foo bar'.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('span').remAtrr('foo'); // Remove single attribute.
$dom('span').remAttr(['foo', 'bar']); // Remove multiple attribute.
$dom('span').remAttr('foo bar'); // Remove multiple attribute.

title: .remove()
name: Remove
description: Remove selected elements.

title: .sortBy()
name: Sort
description: Sort selected elements by attribute value.

Parameter.description: Attribute name.
Options to define value type or sort direction. type: 'string'|'number', direction: 'ascending'|'descending'.

examples.title: Sample #1

title: .val()
name: Val
description: Get the first selected elements value or set all selected elements value.

Parameter.description: Value to set. Leave blank if you want to get the value.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('input[type="text"]').val(); // Get value.
$dom('input[type="text"]').val('Foo'); // Set value to Foo.

title: .append()
name: Append
description: Append childs to first selected elements.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, Array, HTML Formatted String, or String CSS Selector string.

examples.title: Sample #1
Sample #2

title: .appendTo()
name: AppendTo
description: Append selected elements to destination element.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, or CSS Selector string.

title: .clone()
name: Clone
description: Clone selected elements.

title: .html()
name: HTML
description: Get the first selected elements innerHTML or set all selected elements innerHTML.

Parameter.description: Inner html value.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('span').html(); // Get first selected span innerHTML
$dom('span').html('foo'); // Set all span innerHTML to foo.

title: .prepend()
name: Prepend
description: Prepend elements to first selected element.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, Array, HTML Formatted String, or String CSS Selector string.

examples.title: Sample #1
Sample #2

title: .prependTo()
name: PrependTo
description: Prepend selected elements to destination element.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, or CSS Selector string.

title: .text()
name: Text
description: Get the first selected elements innerText or set all selected elements innerText.

Parameter.description: Inner text value.

examples.title: Sample #1
examples.content:
$dom('span').text(); // Get first selected span innerText
$dom('span').text('foo'); // Set all span innerText to foo.

title: .htmls()
name: HTMLs
description: Get selected elements innerHTML

title: .texts()
name: Texts
description: Get selected elements innerText.

title: .insertAfter()
name: insertAfter
description: Insert selected elements after the destination element.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, or CSS Selector string.

title: .insertBefore()
name: insertBefore
description: Insert selected elements before the destination element.

Parameter.description: HTML Element, DOMList, or CSS Selector string.
